Horrible service as they completely messed up our order!  We went there to order for entire family and had a 30 minute drive home.  Had great service with cashier but when order was called for pickup it was in huge bag so we assumed all was there.  Was disappointed because the person who gave us order had just walked in on his shift and was rushing...Wasnt until we got home that we discovered there was only ONE order in the bag and not three (so two of us didnt eat)...smh. We were livid and I called the restaurant back to speak with the manager as I had just wasted over $25 hoping he would rectify the matter by sending a giftcard, etc or something via email or mail to me to rectify the mistake. Soo disappointing.  Will never visit this location again.  Sadly my daughter loves this food, but we will go elsewhere.  Owners need to really re-evaluate their staff.

I do not recommend this location, but other locations may be better.  I ordered online and my food was 25 minutes late. Did I mention they forgot half of the order!?  I called the store back to let them know and I was told that I had to come in to get the rest of my order.  I paid for delivery…  If I wanted to go there I would have in the first place.  I told the guy that I would like the rest of my order delivered and he told me again that I would have to come in.  I asked the guy if he would just refund me for what I lost and he said he would and hung up on me.  Awesome work Wing Stop!

I fell in love with Wing Stop in college. I would order the mild and garlic parm sauce mixed and LOVED the seasoned fries. I was psyched to find out there was one close to me now but was sorely disappointed. First, I ordered online and only had the option to get EITHER mild OR garlic parm on each wing but I figured I could just call after placing my order and specify I wanted the 2 sauces mixed. Did so and was told, rudely, that no they couldn't mix the two. Whatever, I was still excited about the fries. Picked up my order and now I'll never go back. The garlic parm wings had no garlic. It was just a plain wing lightly dusted with the parm you put on your pizza. The fries had absolutely no seasoning on them...just plain fried potatoes. Even my tea from a machine, which just requires you to push a button, was wrong. I pushed "unsweet" and got "raspberry." Never again!!!

Food is great... But my experience there is kinda odd... someone should teach their staff to be courteous enough to call their customers if the orders were cancelled. I ordered online ( order was confirmed) and when I got the store in Bowie, the store was close and the guy in the counter was giving us a sign that they were close... so, he got annoyed and opened the door and ask us why we were there- so we told him we are to pick up the foot we ordered and his reply was (in a very arrogant tone of voice) “we ran of something...” and then we asked him about but we already paid for it? He responded - “it cancelled”. So, we believed him, guess what, after a few days - he charged us in our credit card. FYI: when you order on-line it takes a while for you to get your orders for pick up. From that point of time - the staff working around that time could have called the customers and let them know what’s going on, especially if there is no ingredients or the order was cancelled... my point is, we ordered online for the convenience of doing it and it’s not our fault that you ran out of ingredients or the staff was just feeling lazy to cook ( around 9pm and food to be picked up by 10pm and your store closes at 1145pm). You should have notified us or called us ahead of time!

Wings are pretty good, but someone seriously needs to train the staff how to speak to customers on the phone. Today I called to place a carry out order during which I was interrupted repeatedly, was spoken to like I was bothering them by calling to place an order and with zero respect whatsoever, at the end of the train wreck of this one sided conversation they spewed out something that I think was how long the order would take and the total- I could barely decipher what they were saying because they mumbled with an attitude the whole time- and then they very quickly hung up the phone on me. For this reason alone I will no longer be calling in carry out orders from this place, it’s a shame, because all it takes is some basic training and management, or someone to supervise, as clearly no one around this person is holding them accountable. I’ve been in customer service for years and what I experienced today is just plain bad business, and as a first time customer it has completely turned me off to ever returning.
